# Codex workflow reference

## Session defaults

- Plain `codex` starts with `{{ .agents.codex.defaults.model }}` at {{ .agents.codex.defaults.model_reasoning_effort }} reasoning effort.
- `/model` changes the model or reasoning effort for the current session only; a new
  session returns to the managed defaults.
- No launch profiles are configured. Start with plain `codex` and make any temporary
  session changes in the TUI.
- Plan mode is selected per session; this setup does not persist a default mode
  override.
- `/fast` is a separate speed toggle, not a model or reasoning-effort profile.

## Limits

- Subscription metering (last verified 2026-07): usage counts actual tokens
  against a weekly window — the binding constraint (the 5-hour window is
  currently lifted) — shared across CLI, IDE extension, and cloud tasks.
- Reasoning effort scales burn directly: drop effort per session via `/model`
  for routine work instead of changing the managed default.
- Attached MCP servers reload their full tool schemas every turn — an accepted
  cost here; revisit the server list if the weekly limit starts binding.

## Subagents

- Named specialists under `~/.codex/agents` stay pinned to their configured model tier,
  even after `/model` changes the parent session.
